The paper focuses on energy harvesting maximization in MIMO wiretap channels, which involves information theory (IT) and security (CR) aspects of wireless communication systems. It also deals with resource allocation strategies, which falls under the networked systems (NI) and control systems (SY) categories. Additionally, the paper considers multi-antenna systems, which is a topic in multimedia (MM) communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
